{"title_page": "Paul Hollywood", "text_new": "{{short description|English baker and chef}}\n{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox chef\n| name           = Paul Hollywood \n| image          = Paul_Hollywood.jpg\n| caption        = Hollywood at the<br/>Liverpool Food and Drink Festival, 2012\n| birth_name     = Paul John Hollywood\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1966|3|1}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.imdb.com/name/nm2976349/|title=Paul Hollywood|website=IMDb|accessdate=29 December 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_place    = [[Wallasey]], [[Cheshire]],{{efn|name=\"county\"|In 1966 when Hollywood was born [[Wallasey]] was part of [[Cheshire]], in the [[Local Government Act 1972|local government re-organisation of 1974]] it became part of [[Merseyside]]}}<!--Merseyside came into existence in 1974. Hollywood was born in 1966 when Wallasey was in Cheshire. Therefore Cheshire is correct. Do not change in future--> England\n| style          = Baking\n| education      = \n| television     = {{plainlist|\n*''Paul Hollywood: City Bakes''\n*''[[Paul Hollywood's Pies and Puds]]''\n*''[[The Great British Bake Off]]''\n*''[[The American Baking Competition]]''\n*''Use Your Loaf''\n*''Paul Hollywood's Bread''\n*''[[The Great American Baking Show]]''\n*''Paul Hollywood: A Bakers Life''\n*''Paul Hollywood's Big Continental Road Trip''\n}}\n| awards         = {{plainlist|\n*[[Gourmand World Cookbook Awards]] Top Bread and Pastry Book (2005)\n}}\n| residence      = [[Kent]]\n| spouse         = {{marriage|Alexandra Hollywood|1998|2017}}\n| children       = 1\n| website        = {{website|paulhollywood.com|Official website}}\n}}\n'''Paul John Hollywood''' (born 1 March 1966) is an English [[celebrity chef]] and television presenter, best known for being a judge on ''[[The Great British Bake Off]]''  since 2010.\n\nHe began his career at his father's bakery as a teenager and went on to serve as head baker at a number of hotels around Britain and internationally. After returning from working in [[Cyprus]], Hollywood began appearing in guest spots on a number of British television programmes on both [[BBC]] and [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]. Although Hollywood's broadcast career began with food programming he has since branched out into other genres, including motoring.\n\n==Early life, education and early career==\nPaul John Hollywood was born in 1966 in [[Wallasey]],<ref>[https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/showbiz-news/wallasey-baker-paul-hollywood-described-6257254  \"Wallasey baker Paul Hollywood described affair as 'the biggest mistake of my life'\", ''Liverpool Echo'', 30 October 2013]</ref><ref>[https://www.wirralglobe.co.uk/news/14696990.Wallasey-born_Bake_Off_star_Paul_Hollywood_issues_Top_Gear_charity_race_challenge/  \"Wallasey-born Bake Off star Paul Hollywood issues Top Gear charity race challenge\", ''Wirral Globe'', 22 August 2016]</ref> [[Wirral Peninsula|Wirral]], Cheshire,{{efn|name=\"county\"}} the son of bakery proprietor John F. Hollywood and Gillian M. Harman.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hollywood |first1=Paul |title=A Baker's Life: 100 fantastic recipes, from childhood bakes to five-star excellence |date=2017 |publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing |isbn=978-1408846506}}</ref>  He was a pupil at [[The Mosslands School]]. Hollywood studied sculpture at the Wallasey School of Art but left the school to start work as a baker. He first worked in his father's bakery in York (the headquarters of a chain called Bread Winner which eventually stretched all the way down the east coast from Aberdeen to Lincolnshire) and then in other bakeries on [[Merseyside]].<ref name=wallaseychefecho>{{cite news|last=Coligan |first=Nick |title=Wallasey chef Paul Hollywood on his role in The Great British Bake-Off |url=http://www.wirralnews.co.uk/wirral-news/local-wirral-news/2011/09/20/wallasey-chef-peter-hollywood-on-his-role-in-the-great-british-bake-off-100252-29452213/ |accessdate=31 March 2012 |newspaper=Liverpool Echo |date=20 September 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120329235036/http://www.wirralnews.co.uk/wirral-news/local-wirral-news/2011/09/20/wallasey-chef-peter-hollywood-on-his-role-in-the-great-british-bake-off-100252-29452213/ |archivedate=29 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>  He eventually went on to become head baker at a number of hotels including [[The Dorchester]], [[Chester Grosvenor and Spa]], and the [[Cliveden|Cliveden Hotel]]. He then left the UK for [[Cyprus]], where he worked at two resorts.<ref name=\"uktvbiography\">{{cite web|title = Paul Hollywood|url = http://goodfood.uktv.co.uk/people/paul-hollywood/|publisher = UKTV Food|accessdate = 31 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Television and media career==\nHollywood has appeared in guest spots on a number of television programmes, including [[BBC One]]'s ''[[The Generation Game]]'', ''[[The Heaven and Earth Show]],'' [[ITV Network|ITV]]'s [[This Morning (TV series)|''This Morning'']],<ref name=\"uktvbiography\" /> and ''[[The Alan Titchmarsh Show]]''.<ref name=\"piledonpounds\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/editors-choice/2012/03/06/celebrity-chef-paul-hollywood-i-piled-on-the-pounds-during-the-great-british-bake-off-86908-23777527/|title=Celebrity chef Paul Hollywood: I piled on the pounds during the Great British Bake Off|last=Greenaway|first=Heather|date=6 March 2012|newspaper=The Daily Record|accessdate=31 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307212117/http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk:80/news/editors-choice/2012/03/06/celebrity-chef-paul-hollywood-i-piled-on-the-pounds-during-the-great-british-bake-off-86908-23777527/|archive-date=7 March 2012}}</ref> Since the show launched in 2010, Hollywood has been a judge on the [[BBC]] programme ''[[The Great British Bake Off]]''. In this capacity, he has been described as the \"antidote\" to judges such as [[Len Goodman]] or [[Simon Cowell]] in other reality television programmes, on account of his straightforward and honest manner and because his judging is restricted purely to the finished product.<ref name=risingstarguardian>{{cite news|last=Heritidge|first=Stuart|title=Paul Hollywood: TV's rising star|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2010/sep/15/paul-hollywood-the-great-british-bake-off|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=The Guardian|date=15 September 2010|location=London}}</ref> His partnership with [[Mary Berry (food writer)|Mary Berry]] has been described in ''[[The Guardian]]'' as being the \"secret weapon\" of the show and potentially one of the best judging combinations to have appeared on reality television.<ref name=besteverguardian>{{cite news|last=Hertidge|first=Stuart|title=Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood: the best reality TV judges ever?|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2011/sep/07/berry-hollywood-bake-off-judges|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=The Guardian|date=7 September 2011|location=London}}</ref> In September 2016, [[Love Productions]] agreed to a three-year deal to move the show from the BBC to [[Channel 4]].<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/09/12/bbc-loses-great-british-bake-off/|title = BBC loses Great British Bake Off, as Channel 4 swoops for corporation's biggest show|last = Foster|first = Patrick|date = 12 September 2016|work = [[The Daily Telegraph]]|publisher = [[Telegraph Media Group]]|accessdate = 12 September 2016}}</ref> Hosts [[Mel Giedroyc]] and [[Sue Perkins]] announced that they would not be moving to the new network,<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-37355065|title = Great British Bake Off: Mel and Sue to quit as hosts|date = 13 September 2016|newspaper = [[BBC News]]|accessdate = 13 September 2016}}</ref> followed shortly after by Berry.<ref>{{Cite news|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-37437907|title = Mary Berry to leave Bake Off ahead of Channel 4 move|date = 22 September 2016|newspaper = [[BBC News]]|accessdate = 22 September 2016}}</ref> On the same day as Berry, Hollywood announced that he would be staying with the show.<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2016/sep/22/mary-berry-leave-great-british-bake-off-paul-hollywood-bbc-mel-giedroyc-sue-perkins|title = Mary Berry to leave Bake Off &ndash; but Paul Hollywood agrees to stay|first = Jane|last = Martinson|date = 22 September 2016|accessdate = 23 September 2016|newspaper = [[The Guardian]]}}</ref>\n\nThe Gourmand World Cookbook Awards named his 2005 book ''100 Great Breads'' as the \"Top Bread and Pastry Book\" for that year.<ref name=bbcgood/>\n\nIn 2008, Hollywood created an [[almond]] and [[roquefort]] [[sourdough]] recipe that was said to be the most expensive bread in Britain.<ref name=expensiveloaf/> The roquefort is supplied from a specialist in France at \u00a315 per kilo, while the flour for the bread is made by a [[miller]] in Wiltshire. Hollywood describes it as a \"[[List of Rolls-Royce motor cars|Rolls-Royce]] of loaves\".<ref name=\"expensiveloaf\">{{cite news|last=Cockcroft|first=Lucy|title=Britain's most expensive bread goes on sale at Harrods for \u00a315 a loaf|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/howaboutthat/3661701/Britains-most-expensive-bread-goes-on-sale-at-Harrods-for-15-a-loaf.html|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|date=8 December 2008}}</ref> Hollywood is a guest speaker at several [[food festival]]s, including the Cumbrian Food Festival,<ref>{{cite news|title=Bake Off Star Paul Hollywood Guest at Cumbrian Food Festival |url=http://www.newsandstar.co.uk/features/food-drink/bake-off-star-paul-hollywood-guest-at-cumbrian-food-festival-1.894459?referrerPath=features/food-drink |accessdate=31 March 2012 |newspaper=News and Star |date=5 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120522202511/http://www.newsandstar.co.uk/features/food-drink/bake-off-star-paul-hollywood-guest-at-cumbrian-food-festival-1.894459?referrerPath=features%2Ffood-drink |archivedate=22 May 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and the BBC Good Food Show and the Cake and Bake Show, both in London.<ref name=bbcgood>{{cite web|title=Paul Hollywood |url=http://www.bbcgoodfoodshow.com/paul-hollywood |publisher=BBC Good Food Show |accessdate=31 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111229191537/http://www.bbcgoodfoodshow.com/paul-hollywood |archivedate=29 December 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Paul Hollywood |url=http://thecakeandbakeshow.co.uk/star-speakers/paul-hollywood/ |publisher=The Cake and Bake Show |accessdate=31 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120121013539/http://thecakeandbakeshow.co.uk/star-speakers/paul-hollywood/ |archivedate=21 January 2012 }}</ref> In May 2013, Hollywood began appearing as a judge on ''[[The American Baking Competition]]'' on [[CBS]].\n\nHollywood has also starred in ''[[Sadie J]]'', a children's television programme. In 2013, he presented ''Paul Hollywood\u2019s Bread'' on [[BBC Two]], in which he gave advice on recipes for different types of bread; however, also featured on the series were recipes for some cakes such as the [[Danish pastry]]. He also presented ''[[Paul Hollywood's Pies and Puds]]'', a cookery television series on BBC One.\n\nIn August 2015 Hollywood was featured on the BBC genealogy documentary series ''[[Who Do You Think You Are? (UK TV series)|Who Do You Think You Are?]]'' The programme revealed that his grandfather Norman Harman, who served in the Army during [[World War II]], saw action in the [[Tunisia Campaign]] and at the [[Battle of Anzio]] and that his great-great-grandfather, Kenneth MacKenzie, had been a policeman in the [[City of Glasgow Police]] in the 1850s. Hollywood's great-great-great-grandfather, Donald MacKenzie, had been a [[croft (land)|crofter]] in [[Poolewe]], [[Wester Ross]]. Donald had also been the post-runner between Poolewe and [[Dingwall]], where he delivered post on foot over a distance of {{convert|60|miles|km}}. He covered this distance every week, during his forties, on foot for over a decade. He lived into his 80s.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0664g25 |title=BBC One - Who Do You Think You Are?, Series 12, Paul Hollywood |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=13 August 2015 |accessdate=14 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn May and June 2017 he presented ''Paul Hollywood's Big Continental Road Trip''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/may/27/paul-hollywood-big-continental-trip|title=Paul Hollywood\u2019s Big Continental Trip \u2013 like watching a lifer on day release|last=Sturges|first=Fiona|date=2017-05-27|website=the Guardian|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> In December 2017, Hollywood appeared as a judge on ''[[The Great American Baking Show]]'', the second incarnation of the ''GBBO'' series in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title='The Great American Baking Show' Premieres Thursday, December 7|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/the-great-american-baking-show/news/news/the-great-american-baking-show-premieres-thursday-december-7|website=ABC|accessdate=27 October 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028093933/http://abc.go.com/shows/the-great-american-baking-show/news/news/the-great-american-baking-show-premieres-thursday-december-7|archivedate=28 October 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Motor racing==\nIn 2015 Hollywood began his racing career, making his debut in the [[Beechdean Motorsport|Beechdean AMR]] [[Aston Martin]] Vantage GT4 with Andrew Howard, founder of Beechdean Dairies. The pair qualified second in the [[Britcar]] Trophy Championship's first round at [[Silverstone]] taking second in class in both races.<ref name=\"Timing and Scoring Limited\">[http://www.tsl-timing.com/file/?f=BARC/2015/151321bit.pdf tsl-timing.com], Britcar Trophy Championship, Silverstone, 03/29/2015</ref> He also competed at Le Mans in 2015 in the Aston Martin festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sportscarillustrated.com/News_2015/I/news15I_0884.html|title=Aston Martin Racing hosts Michelin Aston Martin Le Mans Festival|last=|first=|date=|website=sportscarillustrated.com|publisher=Sports Car Illustrated Inc.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170904014335/https://www.sportscarillustrated.com/News_2015/I/news15I_0884.html|archive-date=September 4, 2017|url-status=|accessdate=November 5, 2015}}</ref> Hollywood has also competed in [[International GTSprint Series|GT Cup]] with [[Jonathan Adam|Jonny Adam]] and finished first in class.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beechdeanmotorsport.co.uk/paul-hollywood-jonny-adam-class-win-in-gt-cup/|title=GT cup2 Beechdean AMR GT4 Car Baking Hot with Paul Hollywood\u2019s GT Cup Class Win|last1=Rainbow|first1=Lottie|date=|website=www.beechdeanmotosport.co.uk|publisher=Beechdean Motosport|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180218144040/http://www.beechdeanmotorsport.co.uk:80/paul-hollywood-jonny-adam-class-win-in-gt-cup/|archive-date=18 February 2018|url-status=|accessdate=5 November 2015}}</ref> He entered the British GT championship in 2016 and competed in the last three rounds with [[Jamie Chadwick]] as his driving partner. In July 2017 he came first in class at the Dunlop endurance race at Silverstone in an [[Aston Martin GT4]], and in November 2017 he raced in his first 24 hr race at [[Circuit of the Americas]] coming second in class in an [[Aston Martin GT8]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHollywood met his future wife, Alexandra (Alex), in Cyprus where he was a head baker at a five star hotel and she was a [[scuba diving]] instructor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/560193/Bake-Off-star-Paul-Hollywood-s-wife-Alex-cook-book-My-Busy-Kitchen|title=Paul Hollywood's wife Alex proves she's the hottest cook in the kitchen|last=Nicholas|first=Sadie|date=2015-02-25|work=Express.co.uk|access-date=2017-06-02}}</ref> They later married on the island.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/style/739017/Great-British-Bake-Off-star-Paul-Hollywood-wife-Alex-fashion-secrets|title=In the closet with Great British Bake Off star Paul Hollywood's wife Alex|first=Laura|last=Mulley|date=4 December 2016|publisher=|accessdate=29 December 2017}}</ref> Paul and Alex separated in 2013, after he admitted to an affair with his ''[[The American Baking Competition]]'' co-host [[Marcela Valladolid]], reconciled, then separated again in November 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Paul Hollywood splits from his wife after 20 years|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-42058736|website=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=November 30, 2017|date=November 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Ruby|first1=Jennifer|title=Paul Hollywood announces split from wife Alexandra after nearly 20 years of marriage|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/paul-hollywood-announces-split-from-wife-alexandra-after-nearly-20-years-of-marriage-a3696691.html|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|date=November 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Great British Bake Off host Paul Hollywood and wife separate|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/20/great-british-bake-host-paul-hollywood-wife-separate/|newspaper=[[Daily Telegraph]]|date=November 20, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Metro20171120\">{{cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/11/20/paul-hollywood-and-wife-alex-to-split-after-nearly-20-years-of-marriage-7094458/|title=Paul Hollywood and wife Alex to split after nearly 20 years of marriage|publisher=Metro|last=Westbrook|first=Caroline|access-date=7 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n*''100 Great Breads'' (2004) Cassell, London {{ISBN|978-1-8440-3700-1}}\n*''How to Bake'' (2012) Bloomsbury {{ISBN|978-1-4088-1949-4}}\n*''Paul Hollywood\u2019s Bread'' (2013) Bloomsbury, London {{ISBN|978-1-4088-4069-6}}\n*''Paul Hollywood\u2019s Pies and Puds'' (2013) Bloomsbury, London {{ISBN|978-1-4088-4643-8}}\n*''Paul Hollywood\u2019s British Baking'' (2014) Bloomsbury USA {{ISBN|1408846489}} {{ISBN|978-1408846483}}\n*''The Weekend Baker'' (2016) [[Michael Joseph (publisher)|Michael Joseph]], London {{ISBN|978-0-718-18401-8}} goo gog a\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://paulhollywood.com/}}\n*[https://www.netflix.com/title/80199032''Paul Hollywood's Big Continental Road Trip''] on [[Netflix]]\n*{{IMDb name|id=2976349}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hollywood, Paul}}\n[[Category:British bakers]]\n[[Category:English television chefs]]\n[[Category:People from Wallasey]]\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:BBC television presenters]]\n[[Category:Britcar drivers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English baker and chef}}\n{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox chef\n| name           = Paul Hollywood \n| image          = Paul_Hollywood.jpg\n| caption        = Hollywood at the<br/>Liverpool Food and Drink Festival, 2012\n| birth_name     = Paul John Hollywood\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1966|3|1}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.imdb.com/name/nm2976349/|title=Paul Hollywood|website=IMDb|accessdate=29 December 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_place    = [[Wallasey]], [[Cheshire]],{{efn|name=\"county\"|In 1966 when Hollywood was born [[Wallasey]] was part of [[Cheshire]], in the [[Local Government Act 1972|local government re-organisation of 1974]] it became part of [[Merseyside]]}}<!--Merseyside came into existence in 1974. Hollywood was born in 1966 when Wallasey was in Cheshire. Therefore Cheshire is correct. Do not change in future--> England\n| style          = Baking\n| education      = \n| television     = {{plainlist|\n*''Paul Hollywood: City Bakes''\n*''[[Paul Hollywood's Pies and Puds]]''\n*''[[The Great British Bake Off]]''\n*''[[The American Baking Competition]]''\n*''Use Your Loaf''\n*''Paul Hollywood's Bread''\n*''[[The Great American Baking Show]]''\n*''Paul Hollywood: A Bakers Life''\n*''Paul Hollywood's Big Continental Road Trip''\n}}\n| awards         = {{plainlist|\n*[[Gourmand World Cookbook Awards]] Top Bread and Pastry Book (2005)\n}}\n| residence      = [[Kent]]\n| spouse         = {{marriage|Alexandra Hollywood|1998|2017}}\n| children       = 1\n| website        = {{website|paulhollywood.com|Official website}}\n}}\n'''Paul John Hollywood''' (born 1 March 1966) is an English [[celebrity chef]] and television presenter, best known for being a judge on ''[[The Great British Bake Off]]''  since 2010.\n\nHe began his career at his father's bakery as a teenager and went on to serve as head baker at a number of hotels around Britain and internationally. After returning from working in [[Cyprus]], Hollywood began appearing in guest spots on a number of British television programmes on both [[BBC]] and [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]. Although Hollywood's broadcast career began with food programming he has since branched out into other genres, including motoring.\n\n==Early life, education and early career==\nPaul John Hollywood was born in 1966 in [[Wallasey]],<ref>[https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/showbiz-news/wallasey-baker-paul-hollywood-described-6257254  \"Wallasey baker Paul Hollywood described affair as 'the biggest mistake of my life'\", ''Liverpool Echo'', 30 October 2013]</ref><ref>[https://www.wirralglobe.co.uk/news/14696990.Wallasey-born_Bake_Off_star_Paul_Hollywood_issues_Top_Gear_charity_race_challenge/  \"Wallasey-born Bake Off star Paul Hollywood issues Top Gear charity race challenge\", ''Wirral Globe'', 22 August 2016]</ref> [[Wirral Peninsula|Wirral]], Cheshire,{{efn|name=\"county\"}} the son of bakery proprietor John F. Hollywood and Gillian M. Harman.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hollywood |first1=Paul |title=A Baker's Life: 100 fantastic recipes, from childhood bakes to five-star excellence |date=2017 |publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing |isbn=978-1408846506}}</ref>  He was a pupil at [[The Mosslands School]]. Hollywood studied sculpture at the Wallasey School of Art but left the school to start work as a baker. He first worked in his father's bakery in York (the headquarters of a chain called Bread Winner which eventually stretched all the way down the east coast from Aberdeen to Lincolnshire) and then in other bakeries on [[Merseyside]].<ref name=wallaseychefecho>{{cite news|last=Coligan |first=Nick |title=Wallasey chef Paul Hollywood on his role in The Great British Bake-Off |url=http://www.wirralnews.co.uk/wirral-news/local-wirral-news/2011/09/20/wallasey-chef-peter-hollywood-on-his-role-in-the-great-british-bake-off-100252-29452213/ |accessdate=31 March 2012 |newspaper=Liverpool Echo |date=20 September 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120329235036/http://www.wirralnews.co.uk/wirral-news/local-wirral-news/2011/09/20/wallasey-chef-peter-hollywood-on-his-role-in-the-great-british-bake-off-100252-29452213/ |archivedate=29 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>  He eventually went on to become head baker at a number of hotels including [[The Dorchester]], [[Chester Grosvenor and Spa]], and the [[Cliveden|Cliveden Hotel]]. He then left the UK for [[Cyprus]], where he worked at two resorts.<ref name=\"uktvbiography\">{{cite web|title = Paul Hollywood|url = http://goodfood.uktv.co.uk/people/paul-hollywood/|publisher = UKTV Food|accessdate = 31 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Television and media career==\nHollywood has appeared in guest spots on a number of television programmes, including [[BBC One]]'s ''[[The Generation Game]]'', ''[[The Heaven and Earth Show]],'' [[ITV Network|ITV]]'s [[This Morning (TV series)|''This Morning'']],<ref name=\"uktvbiography\" /> and ''[[The Alan Titchmarsh Show]]''.<ref name=\"piledonpounds\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/editors-choice/2012/03/06/celebrity-chef-paul-hollywood-i-piled-on-the-pounds-during-the-great-british-bake-off-86908-23777527/|title=Celebrity chef Paul Hollywood: I piled on the pounds during the Great British Bake Off|last=Greenaway|first=Heather|date=6 March 2012|newspaper=The Daily Record|accessdate=31 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307212117/http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk:80/news/editors-choice/2012/03/06/celebrity-chef-paul-hollywood-i-piled-on-the-pounds-during-the-great-british-bake-off-86908-23777527/|archive-date=7 March 2012}}</ref> Since the show launched in 2010, Hollywood has been a judge on the [[BBC]] programme ''[[The Great British Bake Off]]''. In this capacity, he has been described as the \"antidote\" to judges such as [[Len Goodman]] or [[Simon Cowell]] in other reality television programmes, on account of his straightforward and honest manner and because his judging is restricted purely to the finished product.<ref name=risingstarguardian>{{cite news|last=Heritidge|first=Stuart|title=Paul Hollywood: TV's rising star|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2010/sep/15/paul-hollywood-the-great-british-bake-off|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=The Guardian|date=15 September 2010|location=London}}</ref> His partnership with [[Mary Berry (food writer)|Mary Berry]] has been described in ''[[The Guardian]]'' as being the \"secret weapon\" of the show and potentially one of the best judging combinations to have appeared on reality television.<ref name=besteverguardian>{{cite news|last=Hertidge|first=Stuart|title=Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood: the best reality TV judges ever?|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2011/sep/07/berry-hollywood-bake-off-judges|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=The Guardian|date=7 September 2011|location=London}}</ref> In September 2016, [[Love Productions]] agreed to a three-year deal to move the show from the BBC to [[Channel 4]].<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/09/12/bbc-loses-great-british-bake-off/|title = BBC loses Great British Bake Off, as Channel 4 swoops for corporation's biggest show|last = Foster|first = Patrick|date = 12 September 2016|work = [[The Daily Telegraph]]|publisher = [[Telegraph Media Group]]|accessdate = 12 September 2016}}</ref> Hosts [[Mel Giedroyc]] and [[Sue Perkins]] announced that they would not be moving to the new network,<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-37355065|title = Great British Bake Off: Mel and Sue to quit as hosts|date = 13 September 2016|newspaper = [[BBC News]]|accessdate = 13 September 2016}}</ref> followed shortly after by Berry.<ref>{{Cite news|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-37437907|title = Mary Berry to leave Bake Off ahead of Channel 4 move|date = 22 September 2016|newspaper = [[BBC News]]|accessdate = 22 September 2016}}</ref> On the same day as Berry, Hollywood announced that he would be staying with the show.<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2016/sep/22/mary-berry-leave-great-british-bake-off-paul-hollywood-bbc-mel-giedroyc-sue-perkins|title = Mary Berry to leave Bake Off &ndash; but Paul Hollywood agrees to stay|first = Jane|last = Martinson|date = 22 September 2016|accessdate = 23 September 2016|newspaper = [[The Guardian]]}}</ref>\n\nThe Gourmand World Cookbook Awards named his 2005 book ''100 Great Breads'' as the \"Top Bread and Pastry Book\" for that year.<ref name=bbcgood/>\n\nIn 2008, Hollywood created an [[almond]] and [[roquefort]] [[sourdough]] recipe that was said to be the most expensive bread in Britain.<ref name=expensiveloaf/> The roquefort is supplied from a specialist in France at \u00a315 per kilo, while the flour for the bread is made by a [[miller]] in Wiltshire. Hollywood describes it as a \"[[List of Rolls-Royce motor cars|Rolls-Royce]] of loaves\".<ref name=\"expensiveloaf\">{{cite news|last=Cockcroft|first=Lucy|title=Britain's most expensive bread goes on sale at Harrods for \u00a315 a loaf|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/howaboutthat/3661701/Britains-most-expensive-bread-goes-on-sale-at-Harrods-for-15-a-loaf.html|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=The Daily Telegraph|date=8 December 2008}}</ref> Hollywood is a guest speaker at several [[food festival]]s, including the Cumbrian Food Festival,<ref>{{cite news|title=Bake Off Star Paul Hollywood Guest at Cumbrian Food Festival |url=http://www.newsandstar.co.uk/features/food-drink/bake-off-star-paul-hollywood-guest-at-cumbrian-food-festival-1.894459?referrerPath=features/food-drink |accessdate=31 March 2012 |newspaper=News and Star |date=5 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120522202511/http://www.newsandstar.co.uk/features/food-drink/bake-off-star-paul-hollywood-guest-at-cumbrian-food-festival-1.894459?referrerPath=features%2Ffood-drink |archivedate=22 May 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and the BBC Good Food Show and the Cake and Bake Show, both in London.<ref name=bbcgood>{{cite web|title=Paul Hollywood |url=http://www.bbcgoodfoodshow.com/paul-hollywood |publisher=BBC Good Food Show |accessdate=31 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111229191537/http://www.bbcgoodfoodshow.com/paul-hollywood |archivedate=29 December 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Paul Hollywood |url=http://thecakeandbakeshow.co.uk/star-speakers/paul-hollywood/ |publisher=The Cake and Bake Show |accessdate=31 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120121013539/http://thecakeandbakeshow.co.uk/star-speakers/paul-hollywood/ |archivedate=21 January 2012 }}</ref> In May 2013, Hollywood began appearing as a judge on ''[[The American Baking Competition]]'' on [[CBS]].\n\nHollywood has also starred in ''[[Sadie J]]'', a children's television programme. In 2013, he presented ''Paul Hollywood\u2019s Bread'' on [[BBC Two]], in which he gave advice on recipes for different types of bread; however, also featured on the series were recipes for some cakes such as the [[Danish pastry]]. He also presented ''[[Paul Hollywood's Pies and Puds]]'', a cookery television series on BBC One.\n\nIn August 2015 Hollywood was featured on the BBC genealogy documentary series ''[[Who Do You Think You Are? (UK TV series)|Who Do You Think You Are?]]'' The programme revealed that his grandfather Norman Harman, who served in the Army during [[World War II]], saw action in the [[Tunisia Campaign]] and at the [[Battle of Anzio]] and that his great-great-grandfather, Kenneth MacKenzie, had been a policeman in the [[City of Glasgow Police]] in the 1850s. Hollywood's great-great-great-grandfather, Donald MacKenzie, had been a [[croft (land)|crofter]] in [[Poolewe]], [[Wester Ross]]. Donald had also been the post-runner between Poolewe and [[Dingwall]], where he delivered post on foot over a distance of {{convert|60|miles|km}}. He covered this distance every week, during his forties, on foot for over a decade. He lived into his 80s.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0664g25 |title=BBC One - Who Do You Think You Are?, Series 12, Paul Hollywood |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=13 August 2015 |accessdate=14 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn May and June 2017 he presented ''Paul Hollywood's Big Continental Road Trip''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/may/27/paul-hollywood-big-continental-trip|title=Paul Hollywood\u2019s Big Continental Trip \u2013 like watching a lifer on day release|last=Sturges|first=Fiona|date=2017-05-27|website=the Guardian|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> In December 2017, Hollywood appeared as a judge on ''[[The Great American Baking Show]]'', the second incarnation of the ''GBBO'' series in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title='The Great American Baking Show' Premieres Thursday, December 7|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/the-great-american-baking-show/news/news/the-great-american-baking-show-premieres-thursday-december-7|website=ABC|accessdate=27 October 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028093933/http://abc.go.com/shows/the-great-american-baking-show/news/news/the-great-american-baking-show-premieres-thursday-december-7|archivedate=28 October 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Motor racing==\nIn 2015 Hollywood began his racing career, making his debut in the [[Beechdean Motorsport|Beechdean AMR]] [[Aston Martin]] Vantage GT4 with Andrew Howard, founder of Beechdean Dairies. The pair qualified second in the [[Britcar]] Trophy Championship's first round at [[Silverstone]] taking second in class in both races.<ref name=\"Timing and Scoring Limited\">[http://www.tsl-timing.com/file/?f=BARC/2015/151321bit.pdf tsl-timing.com], Britcar Trophy Championship, Silverstone, 03/29/2015</ref> He also competed at Le Mans in 2015 in the Aston Martin festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sportscarillustrated.com/News_2015/I/news15I_0884.html|title=Aston Martin Racing hosts Michelin Aston Martin Le Mans Festival|last=|first=|date=|website=sportscarillustrated.com|publisher=Sports Car Illustrated Inc.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170904014335/https://www.sportscarillustrated.com/News_2015/I/news15I_0884.html|archive-date=September 4, 2017|url-status=|accessdate=November 5, 2015}}</ref> Hollywood has also competed in [[International GTSprint Series|GT Cup]] with [[Jonathan Adam|Jonny Adam]] and finished first in class.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beechdeanmotorsport.co.uk/paul-hollywood-jonny-adam-class-win-in-gt-cup/|title=GT cup2 Beechdean AMR GT4 Car Baking Hot with Paul Hollywood\u2019s GT Cup Class Win|last1=Rainbow|first1=Lottie|date=|website=www.beechdeanmotosport.co.uk|publisher=Beechdean Motosport|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180218144040/http://www.beechdeanmotorsport.co.uk:80/paul-hollywood-jonny-adam-class-win-in-gt-cup/|archive-date=18 February 2018|url-status=|accessdate=5 November 2015}}</ref> He entered the British GT championship in 2016 and competed in the last three rounds with [[Jamie Chadwick]] as his driving partner. In July 2017 he came first in class at the Dunlop endurance race at Silverstone in an [[Aston Martin GT4]], and in November 2017 he raced in his first 24 hr race at [[Circuit of the Americas]] coming second in class in an [[Aston Martin GT8]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHollywood met his future wife, Alexandra (Alex), in Cyprus where he was a head baker at a five star hotel and she was a [[scuba diving]] instructor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/560193/Bake-Off-star-Paul-Hollywood-s-wife-Alex-cook-book-My-Busy-Kitchen|title=Paul Hollywood's wife Alex proves she's the hottest cook in the kitchen|last=Nicholas|first=Sadie|date=2015-02-25|work=Express.co.uk|access-date=2017-06-02}}</ref> They later married on the island.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/style/739017/Great-British-Bake-Off-star-Paul-Hollywood-wife-Alex-fashion-secrets|title=In the closet with Great British Bake Off star Paul Hollywood's wife Alex|first=Laura|last=Mulley|date=4 December 2016|publisher=|accessdate=29 December 2017}}</ref> Paul and Alex separated in 2013, after he admitted to an affair with his ''[[The American Baking Competition]]'' co-host [[Marcela Valladolid]], reconciled, then separated again in November 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Paul Hollywood splits from his wife after 20 years|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-42058736|website=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=November 30, 2017|date=November 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Ruby|first1=Jennifer|title=Paul Hollywood announces split from wife Alexandra after nearly 20 years of marriage|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/paul-hollywood-announces-split-from-wife-alexandra-after-nearly-20-years-of-marriage-a3696691.html|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|date=November 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Great British Bake Off host Paul Hollywood and wife separate|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/20/great-british-bake-host-paul-hollywood-wife-separate/|newspaper=[[Daily Telegraph]]|date=November 20, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Metro20171120\">{{cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/11/20/paul-hollywood-and-wife-alex-to-split-after-nearly-20-years-of-marriage-7094458/|title=Paul Hollywood and wife Alex to split after nearly 20 years of marriage|publisher=Metro|last=Westbrook|first=Caroline|access-date=7 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n*''100 Great Breads'' (2004) Cassell, London {{ISBN|978-1-8440-3700-1}}\n*''How to Bake'' (2012) Bloomsbury {{ISBN|978-1-4088-1949-4}}\n*''Paul Hollywood\u2019s Bread'' (2013) Bloomsbury, London {{ISBN|978-1-4088-4069-6}}\n*''Paul Hollywood\u2019s Pies and Puds'' (2013) Bloomsbury, London {{ISBN|978-1-4088-4643-8}}\n*''Paul Hollywood\u2019s British Baking'' (2014) Bloomsbury USA {{ISBN|1408846489}} {{ISBN|978-1408846483}}\n*''The Weekend Baker'' (2016) [[Michael Joseph (publisher)|Michael Joseph]], London {{ISBN|978-0-718-18401-8}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://paulhollywood.com/}}\n*[https://www.netflix.com/title/80199032''Paul Hollywood's Big Continental Road Trip''] on [[Netflix]]\n*{{IMDb name|id=2976349}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hollywood, Paul}}\n[[Category:British bakers]]\n[[Category:English television chefs]]\n[[Category:People from Wallasey]]\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:BBC television presenters]]\n[[Category:Britcar drivers]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7d:c59d:2c00:e413:850d:3212:fc2b", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eBibliography)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Hollywood"}
